    "discriminators": [
     "A TONAL CHIME THAT DECAYS. The morphology is impulsive_with_tail: an attack into a harmonic body that then RINGS DOWN FREELY (long envelope_decay_seconds, low sustain_ratio). Startup chimes, notification dings, pop-up alerts.",
     "Against UIBeep — the key boundary in this category, and it is an ENVELOPE test, not a spectral one. Both are harmonic and non-noisy, so flatness and harmonicity are useless here. A BEEP is a GATED tone: it holds level and then STOPS (sustain_ratio ~0.75, high envelope_sustain_level, short decay). An ALERT RINGS OUT (sustain_ratio ~0.2, envelope_decay ~0.6 s). Only the envelope decides.",
     "Alerts are frequently MULTI-NOTE (a chime arpeggio, a two-tone notification), so transient_count 2-4 over a stable harmonic spectrum leans ALERT over BEEP.",
     "Against ALRMElec / ALRMBuzr: an ALARM REPEATS AND INSISTS — long, cyclic, high onset_periodicity, designed to be unignorable. An alert fires ONCE and gets out of the way. Duration and periodicity separate them.",
     "Against BELLS: physically the same struck-and-ringing object. Semantically not. Text ('UI', 'notification', 'startup', 'GUI') is required to commit."
    ],
    "confusable_with": [
     "UIBeep",
     "UIMisc",
     "ALRMElec",
     "BEEP",
     "BEEPAppl"
    ]
