    "discriminators": [
     "A SHORT, NEAR-PURE TONE — the purest tonal object in the entire ontology. harmonicity approaching 1.0, spectral_flatness approaching 0.0, a rock-stable f0 that does not drift, and very FEW partials (a piezo sounder or a square-wave generator: partial_count 1-5).",
     "Against UIGlitch and COMStatic: the exact opposite pole of the tonal/noise axis. spectral_flatness alone separates them with a huge margin — this is as easy as classification gets.",
     "Against UIAlert: the ENVELOPE, and only the envelope. A beep is GATED (holds, then stops); an alert RINGS OUT. See UIAlert.",
     "Against UIClick: a click has neither pitch nor sustain; a beep has both, and is 5-10x longer.",
     "Against the BEEPS category: identical physics — UCS itself concedes it, 'Also see BEEPS category.' NOTHING in DSP separates a UI beep from a BEEPS-GENERAL beep; they are the same waveform filed under different intent. Text ('UI', 'interface', 'menu', 'UX') must commit, and where it does not, defer to BEEPS."
    ],
