    "discriminators": [
     "'ON SCREEN GLITCHES OR STATIC' — NOISY AND APERIODIC. The signature is HIGH spectral_flatness (noise-like) combined with HIGH spectral_flux (the spectrum churns, tears, jumps frame to frame). That FLUX is precisely what makes it a glitch rather than a bed of static.",
     "Against COMStatic — the crucial pair, and the one that shows why flatness alone is not enough. STATIC is STATIONARY noise: a flat spectrum that DOES NOT CHANGE (stationarity ~0.9, spectral_flux ~0.08). GLITCH is UNSTABLE noise: EQUALLY flat, but violently NON-stationary (stationarity ~0.3, flux ~0.55). The flatness axis cannot separate them. The flux/stationarity axis separates them cleanly.",
     "Against UIBeep and UIAlert: the tonal versus noise poles of the same category. Trivially separable on flatness and harmonicity.",
     "Against UIData: data is ordered and pitched; glitch is disordered and unpitched. See UIData.",
     "Digital-artefact glitches (bit-crush, buffer repeat, sample-rate tearing) additionally push inharmonicity and total_harmonic_distortion high — a useful secondary confirmation."
