    "discriminators": [
     "SWEPT, NOT STRUCK. Slides, swipes, scrolls, opens, closes, appears, disappears — a UI motion is a single CONTINUOUS GESTURE whose spectrum MOVES. The measurable core is a monotonic spectral trajectory: large spectral_centroid_deviation_hz and a clearly non-zero spectral_centroid_slope_hz_per_second across a single, un-transient-ed event.",
     "The SIGN of that slope carries the open/close, appear/disappear polarity: rising centroid = open / appear / zoom-in, falling = close / disappear / zoom-out. Do NOT gate on sign — the subcategory contains both directions — but a slope of ~0 with no centroid movement argues against UIMvmt entirely, which is why the prior is kept broad and low-weight.",
